### PCA9685 board issues

Fully wired, the servo remains still. Debugging;

Use jumper wires to connect the servo to the Arduino directly; GND to GND, power to Arduino 5V, connect signal only to PCA9685 board and power is taken directly fron arduino... no issues.
Again, the same thing, this time connect the power cable to the PCA9685 board... issue. The servo does not run.
Power supply is working, but power is not getting to the servo; use a jumper cable between the V+ screw terminal directly to the power rail... no issue.

Final Judgment: Soldering is required to connect a wire from the V+ screw terminal to the power rail.
